    "body": "Currently, the type hinting is in Python style and Python doesn't have strict integer size. (e.g., we can't define an \"unsigned 64-bit integer\" variable in Python). In Py-EVM, [we are planning to do more custom typing like `Hash32`](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/issues/1383), and it could be also refect to the spec.\r\n\r\nFor example, in Py-EVM, we will define:\r\n```python\r\nSlotNumber = NewType('SlotNumber', int)  # uint64\r\nShardNumber = NewType('ShardNumber', int)  # uint64\r\nValidatorIndex = NewType('ValidatorIndex', int)  # uint24\r\nGwei = NewType('Gwei', int)  # uint64\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd in the spec, maybe somewhere before `Constants` section:\r\n\r\n### Custom Types\r\n\r\n*(Jan 18th updated)*\r\n\r\nWe define the following custom types for type hinting and readability:\r\n\r\n| Name | Type | Description |\r\n| - | - | - |\r\n| `SlotNumber` | unsigned 64-bit integer | the number of a slot |\r\n| `ShardNumber` | unsigned 64-bit integer | the number of a shard |\r\n| `ValidatorIndex` | unsigned 24-bit integer | the index number of validator in the registry |\r\n| `Gwei` | unsigned 64-bit integer | the amount in Gwei |\r\n| `Bytes32` | 32-byte data | the binary data in 32-byte length |\r\n| `BLSPubkey` | 48-byte data | the public key in BLS signature scheme |\r\n| `BLSSignature` | 96-byte data | the signature in BLS signature scheme |\r\n\r\n...etc.\r\n\r\nAnd in the helper functions, we can use the custom types, e.g.,:\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef min_empty_validator_index(validators: List[ValidatorRecord],\r\n                              validator_balances: List[Gwei],\r\n                              current_slot: SlotNumber) -> ValidatorIndex:\r\n    for i, (v, vbal) in enumerate(zip(validators, validator_balances)):\r\n        if vbal == 0 and v.latest_status_change_slot + ZERO_BALANCE_VALIDATOR_TTL <= current_slot:\r\n            return i\r\n    return None\r\n```\r\n",
